# CEO (Build) Review — AgriPro Operations Console

## Verdict: PASS (target 10/10 met)

Actually built, served, and Playwright-exercised the demo. Both builds green, zero console errors, hero AI flow works end to end.

## Verified working (local, http://localhost:4041/demos/agripro/)
- **Build**: demo `npm run build` PASS (2.6s); michaelwegter.com PASS (5.0s); registry entry `id:20 slug:agripro` valid.
- **Load**: 0 console errors / 0 pageerrors on first paint and across every tab.
- **RBAC (R1)**: 4 roles with distinct scoped nav (Quality->inspections, Mgmt->dashboards+admin, etc.). Verified nav gating per role.
- **Hero AI (R14/R15/R16)**: loaded "Flagged Corn" sample -> classified doc type, extracted Moisture/Aflatoxin/Test Weight, anomaly detector flagged aflatoxin 22.0 ppb above reject band. Real client-side Tesseract.js with 9s timeout + seeded fallback (honest AI). Verified live.
- **Exports (R10)**: PDF download `agripro-management-report.pdf` and Excel `agripro-management-report.xlsx` both fire real downloads (jsPDF + xlsx via dynamic import).
- **Dashboards (R9)**: Recharts SVG charts render per role.
- **Approvals (R5)**: 6-stage pipeline with advance/reject + audit trail.
- **Procurement (R2), Warehouse (R6), Documents (R7/R8), Notifications (R11), Audit (R12)**: all present and populated; audit log live-appends session actions (11 rows).
- **Admin portal (D3)**: Management-only, renders 6 config cards.
- **Mobile (R13)**: real `@media(max-width:768px)` — nav collapses to bottom bar, grids to single column, detail panel to sheet. Verified at 390px.
- **Dash gate**: no em/en dashes in our source (only matches are inside vendored xlsx/jspdf libs). Bespoke agricultural palette (dark green nav, cream bg, IBM Plex Sans/Mono), not michaelwegter.com's look.

## Requirement coverage
All 16 explicit reqs (R1-R16) + admin portal (D3) represented and functional. D4/D5/D6/D7 (docs, testing, deployment, support) are proposal-level deliverables, correctly out of demo scope — flag for proposal-writer to address.

## Non-blocking observations (do NOT loop for these)
- Admin sub-panels and Document View/Download are `alert()` stubs, honestly labeled "full build feature" — acceptable demo affordance at this scope.
- Main JS chunk 623 kB (recharts/tesseract entry); jspdf/xlsx already code-split. Fine for a demo; trim later if trivial.

This is a genuinely full-featured, working, production-shaped app with several real features and honest AI. Meets 10/10.

## handoff
- **Produced**: verified build-ceo pass; demo built at michaelwegter.com/public/demos/agripro/, registry id 20 valid.
- **Decisions**: PASS — no builder loop, no redirect. Frontend-only + client-side Tesseract accepted; no mw-backend changes needed.
- **Next needs**: deploy step pushes michaelwegter.com to main (fire-and-trust, no live poll). Proposal-writer must cover D4-D7 (docs/testing/deployment/post-launch) in cover letter and name the demo URL.
- **Risks**: Tesseract WASM loads from CDN at runtime (~5s first real scan); seeded fallback keeps hero reliable if CDN slow/blocked. Large main chunk (acceptable). Live URL unverifiable from this environment (expected).

VERDICT: pass
